records.addlTxt: Defendant Terrance A Kyles appears by video from Kettle Moraine Correctional.  Attorney Melinda A. Swartz, Defendant's Appellate Counsel, appears by telephone.  Haley Jo Rea appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Matter is before the Court on a Motion to Withdraw as Post-conviction Counsel.  Court explains to Mr. Kyles that it is required to inform him of the ramificiations of his request and the options available to him.  Attorney Swartz makes a record as to her discussions with Mr. Kyles.  The Court did receive a letter from Regional Attorney Manager Joseph Ehmann which was copied to both Attorney Swartz and Mr. Kyles.  Court explains to Mr. Kyles if the Motion to Withdraw is granted, he would have the option to hire an attorney at his own expense or proceed without an Attorney.  Defendant says he has the resources to hire an Attorney.  Court further explains that if the Motion is granted and he is not able to retain an Attorney, he is waiving his right to a public defender at any point in the future in this matter.  Defendant now indicates he is not sure he can hire an Attorney.  He believes it to be 50/50 or 40/60 chance.  Attorney Swartz asks to withdraw her Motion based upon what Mr. Kyles has said in Court today.  Court grants request to withdraw the Motion.
